-- Omers, Alberta Fund Oppose Magna International Buyout Plan, Globe Says
-- Sean B. Pasternak
-- 2010-06-17T11:18:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/omers-alberta-fund-oppose-magna-international-buyout-plan-globe-says.html

          
          
             Three of Canada’s largest
institutional investors oppose an $863 million plan by Magna
International Inc. to buy founder  Frank Stronach ’s controlling
stake in car parts maker, the Globe and Mail reported.  
 The investors are British Columbia Investment Management
Corp., Alberta Investment Management Corp. and the Ontario
Municipal Employees Retirement System, which combined manage
about C$200 billion ($195.3 billion) in assets, the  newspaper 
said, citing unidentified people.  
 The investors join the Canada Pension Plan Investment Board
and other firms in opposing the deal, the Globe said.  
